# Moonshot — Architecture & Flows Reference

**Moonshot** is an AI-powered QA automation platform. It lets users create test suites from app screenshots/text context, generate test cases with AI, and execute them autonomously on real running apps using an AI vision agent.

---

## System Architecture

Three independent services communicate to deliver the full product:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Frontend  (React + Vite, runs in browser)                          │
│  - User-facing UI                                                   │
│  - Calls local backend via HTTP/SSE for AI + execution              │
│  - Calls cloud backend directly for auth + data CRUD               │
└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────┬───────────────────────┘
                       │                      │
          localhost:8000 (SSE+REST)     cloud HTTPS (REST)
                       │                      │
┌──────────────────────▼──────┐  ┌────────────▼──────────────────────┐
│  Local Backend  (FastAPI)   │  │  Cloud Backend  (FastAPI+MongoDB) │
│  - Runs on user's machine   │  │  - Hosted service                 │
│  - Manages AI agents        │  │  - Auth (JWT)                     │
│  - Captures screenshots     │  │  - Persistent data store          │
│  - Executes mouse/keyboard  │  │  - Projects, Features,            │
│  - Orchestrates test runs   │  │    TestCases, TestRuns, Results   │
│  - Calls cloud to save data │  │                                   │
└─────────────────────────────┘  └───────────────────────────────────┘
```

