## Frontend

### Tech Stack

| Layer | Package |
|-------|---------|
| Framework | React 19 + Vite 7 |
| Routing | TanStack Router (file-based, type-safe) |
| Server state | TanStack React Query |
| Client state | Zustand |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui (Radix primitives) |
| HTTP | Axios (REST) + native `fetch` (SSE streams) |
| Icons | lucide-react |
| Animations | motion (Framer Motion) |

### Route Tree

```
/                          → routes/index.tsx       (redirect to /app or /login)
/login                     → routes/login.tsx        (auth page)
/app                       → routes/app.tsx          (layout: sidebar + SidebarInset)
  /app/                    → routes/app/index.tsx    (projects list)
  /app/create              → routes/app/create.tsx   (free-form create, legacy)
  /app/settings            → routes/app/settings.tsx (API key management — add/update/remove Anthropic key)
  /app/execute             → routes/app/execute.tsx  (test suite execution + replay page)
  /app/projects/$projectId → routes/app/projects/$projectId.tsx  (project layout guard — Outlet only)
    /app/projects/$projectId/          → $projectId/index.tsx    (project overview bento)
    /app/projects/$projectId/context   → $projectId/context.tsx  (project AI context page)
    /app/projects/$projectId/tests/    → $projectId/tests/index.tsx  (test suites list)
    /app/projects/$projectId/tests/$featureId → $projectId/tests/$featureId.tsx  (layout guard — Outlet only)
      /app/projects/$projectId/tests/$featureId/       → $featureId/index.tsx   (suite detail page)
      /app/projects/$projectId/tests/$featureId/runs/  → $featureId/runs/index.tsx  (past runs list)
/execute                   → routes/execute.tsx      (redirects to /app/execute if logged in)
```

**`/app/settings`** — the primary place for users to add, update, or remove their Anthropic API key. Uses `save-anthropic-key` / `delete-anthropic-key` IPC calls. Accessible from the sidebar.

**Key routing rule:** In TanStack Router, `foo.tsx` alongside a `foo/` directory becomes the layout route (requires `<Outlet />`). Use `foo/index.tsx` when `foo.tsx` should be an independent index route, not a layout wrapper. Both `$projectId.tsx` and `$featureId.tsx` are pure layout guards that only render `<Outlet />`.

