## Key User Flows

### Flow 1 — Auth

```
/login  →  POST /api/v1/auth/login (cloud)  →  JWT token stored in authStore
                                             →  redirect to /app
```

Guest users can "skip" auth (`skipped = true` in authStore) but cannot use cloud-backed features.

---

### Flow 2 — Project Creation

User fills project name + description + uploads images/text → AI processes them:

```
Frontend (ProjectsSection)
  ↓  POST /cloud/project/create (local backend SSE)
  ↓  streams: "Processing images..." → "Synthesising context..." → "Saving project..."

Local Backend (/cloud/project/create)
  1. Save images + texts as ContextItems  →  POST /api/v1/context-items/bulk (cloud)
  2. Run ImageContextRetrieverAgent on each image  →  extract what each screen shows
  3. Run _SynthAgent with all image contexts + text notes  →  produce context_summary prose
  4. POST /api/v1/projects (cloud)  →  save { name, description, context_summary }
  5. SSE done event  →  { project: { id, name, description, context_summary } }

Frontend
  →  React Query invalidates projects list  →  new project appears
```

**Key file:** `backend/main.py` → `cloud_create_project` endpoint

---

### Flow 3 — Project Context Update

User revisits the project context page and uploads new/updated images + text:

```
Frontend (/app/projects/$projectId/context)
  ↓  POST /cloud/project/{id}/update-context (local backend SSE)

Local Backend
  1. Delete old ContextItems for this project  →  DELETE /api/v1/context-items/by-project/{id} (cloud)
  2. Save new ContextItems  →  POST /api/v1/context-items/bulk (cloud)
  3. Run ImageContextRetrieverAgent + _SynthAgent  →  new context_summary
  4. PATCH /api/v1/projects/{id}  →  update context_summary on cloud
  5. SSE done event
```

**Key file:** `backend/main.py` → `cloud_update_project_context` endpoint

---

### Flow 4 — Test Suite Creation (CreateTestFlow modal)

A 4-step wizard opened from the Test Suites page. All steps operate on a cloud Feature record.

#### Step 1 — Feature Details
User enters feature name + description → `POST /api/v1/features` (cloud, via `createCloudFeature` in `client.ts`) → `cloudFeatureId` stored in component state.

#### Step 2 — Select Assets
User uploads images and/or text notes. These are passed to the context-building step.

#### Step 3 — Build Context (SSE)

```
Frontend  →  POST /cloud/feature/{featureId}/build-context (local backend SSE)
             body: { images[], texts[], user_feedback? }

Local Backend
  IF user_feedback is present (context rebuild):
    1. Fetch existing feature.context_summary from cloud
    2. Build refine_prompt: existing_summary + user_feedback
    3. Run _SynthAgent with refine_prompt  →  updated context_summary (skip image re-analysis)

  ELSE (initial build):
    1. Save images + texts as ContextItems  →  cloud
    2. Run ImageContextRetrieverAgent on each image  →  per-image context
    3. Run _SynthAgent combining all image contexts + text notes  →  context_summary

  4. PATCH /api/v1/features/{id}  →  save context_summary, status = "context_ready"
  5. SSE done  →  { context_summary }

Frontend
  →  shows context_summary prose in Step 3 review panel
  →  user can provide feedback and hit "Rebuild context" to iterate (skips image re-analysis)
  →  when happy: clicks "Awesome! Generate Tests"
```

#### Step 4 — Generate Tests (SSE)

```
Frontend  →  POST /cloud/feature/{featureId}/generate-tests (local backend SSE)
             body: { project_id, token, provider, user_feedback? }

Local Backend
  1. Fetch project.context_summary + feature.context_summary from cloud
  2. Build combined_context = { feature context + project context + user_feedback }
  3. Run TestPlannerAgent.generate_from_feature_context(combined_context)
     - LLM prompt includes: feature summary, project summary, optional USER FEEDBACK block
     - Returns: { feature_summary, test_cases[], coverage_notes }
  4. SSE done  →  { feature_summary, test_cases[], coverage_notes }

Frontend
  →  user reviews test cards (expandable, priority-colored left border)
  →  can toggle individual tests in/out
  →  "Not what you expected?" panel: type feedback → "Regenerate tests" re-calls this flow
  →  "All Good, Save Tests" → calls saveFeatureTests
```

#### Save Tests

```
Frontend  →  saveFeatureTests(featureId, selectedTestCases, token)
           →  DELETE /api/v1/test-cases/by-feature/{id} (cloud)  (clear old tests)
           →  POST /api/v1/test-cases/bulk (cloud)               (save new tests)
           →  PATCH /api/v1/features/{id}  status = "tests_generated"
```

**Key files:**
- `frontend/src/components/CreateTestFlow/CreateTestFlow.tsx`
- `backend/main.py` → `cloud_build_feature_context`, `cloud_generate_feature_tests`
- `backend/agents/test_planner_agent.py`

