## AI Agents (Local Backend)

### ImageContextRetrieverAgent
**File:** `backend/agents/image_context_retriever_agent.py` (called from `context_builder.py`)

Takes a screenshot/image (base64) and extracts structured context:
- Screens detected
- UI elements visible
- User flows implied
- Requirements inferred

Returns prose context for each image.

### _SynthAgent
**File:** `backend/main.py` (inline usage)

Synthesises multiple image contexts + text notes into a single cohesive `context_summary` prose paragraph. Also used for feedback-based context refinement (skips image re-analysis when `user_feedback` is provided).

### TestPlannerAgent
**File:** `backend/agents/test_planner_agent.py`

Generates test cases from feature context. Accepts:
- `context_summary` (feature)
- `project_context` (project-level background)
- `user_feedback` (optional correction to steer generation)

Returns JSON: `{ feature_summary, test_cases[], coverage_notes }`.

Each test case: `{ test_key, title, goal, description, category, priority, expected_result }`.

**Default model:** `claude-haiku-4-5` (cost-optimised for text generation).

### DocumentContextRetrieverAgent
**File:** `backend/agents/document_context_retriever_agent.py`

Extracts structured context from uploaded PDF/document files. Called during feature context build when documents are part of the assets.

### VideoContextRetrieverAgent
**File:** `backend/agents/video_context_retriever_agent.py`

Extracts structured context from uploaded video files (frame sampling + analysis). Called during feature context build when videos are part of the assets.

### ClaudeComputerUseAgent
**File:** `backend/agents/claude_computer_use_agent.py`

Production execution agent. Uses Anthropic's native Computer Use beta to control any macOS application via pixel-accurate coordinates. Unlike Gemini, it works on any desktop app, not just browsers.

**Key behaviours:**
- Accepts an optional `system_prompt` at init (the rich `cu_system_prompt` built from project + feature context)
- `start(goal, screenshot_bytes)` — begins a task, returns `ClaudeCUResponse`
- `step(tool_use_ids, screenshot_bytes)` — continues after executing actions
- `inject_guidance(text)` — queues operator guidance to be sent in the next `step()` call as a top-level user message text block
- Runs synchronous Anthropic API calls via `await asyncio.to_thread()` to avoid blocking the FastAPI event loop (critical for pause/abort to work)

**Default model:** `claude-haiku-4-5`
**Beta flag:** `computer-use-2025-01-24`
**Tool version:** `computer_20250124`

