## Local Backend Key Endpoints

| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |
|----------|--------|---------|
| `/windows` | GET | List currently open OS windows with bounds |
| `/health` | GET | Backend health check |
| `/permissions` | GET | Check Screen Recording + Accessibility grants (from backend process perspective) |
| `/permissions/request` | POST | Attempt to trigger macOS permission dialogs |
| `/cloud/project/create` | POST (SSE) | Create project with AI context |
| `/cloud/project/{id}/update-context` | POST (SSE) | Rebuild project context |
| `/cloud/feature/{id}/build-context` | POST (SSE) | Build or rebuild feature context |
| `/cloud/feature/{id}/generate-tests` | POST (SSE) | Generate test cases via AI |
| `/cloud/feature/{id}/save-tests` | POST | Save a set of test cases to cloud (called after generate) |
| `/feature/{id}/execute` | POST (SSE) | **Production** — execute test suite on a window |
| `/feature/{id}/execute/pause` | POST | Signal backend to pause after current step |
| `/feature/{id}/execute/resume` | POST | Resume a paused execution (optional guidance) |
| `/feature/{id}/execute/abort` | POST | Abort execution loop immediately |
| `/feature/{id}/execute/{test_id}/guidance` | POST | Inject user guidance when agent is stuck |

All SSE endpoints stream `data: { event, ...payload }\n\n` lines.

**`backend/cloud_client.py` — helpers for test run persistence:**

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `create_test_result_early(run_id, test_case_id, token)` | Creates `TestResult` with `status="running"` at test start; returns `{ id, ... }` |
| `append_test_result_step(result_id, step, token)` | Calls `POST /api/v1/test-results/{id}/steps` to atomically push one step dict |
| `patch_test_result(result_id, token, **fields)` | PATCH final `status`, `conclusion`, `steps_executed` on completion |

**Per-execution in-memory state (keyed by `context_id`):**

| Dict | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `pause_flags` | Set to `True` to request a pause |
| `pause_resume_events` | `asyncio.Event` the loop awaits when paused |
| `pause_guidance` | Optional guidance text to inject on resume |
| `guidance_events` | `asyncio.Event` the loop awaits when agent is stuck |
| `guidance_text` | Guidance text submitted by user for stuck agent |
| `abort_flags` | Set to `True` to break the execution loop |

All dicts are cleaned up after the execution generator finishes.

