## Cloud Backend Data Models

| Model | Key Fields |
|-------|------------|
| `User` | `id`, `email`, `hashed_password` |
| `Project` | `id`, `user_id`, `name`, `description`, `context_summary` |
| `Feature` | `id`, `project_id`, `name`, `description`, `context_summary`, `status` |
| `ContextItem` | `id`, `level` (project/feature), `level_id`, `type` (image/text), `content_b64`/`text` |
| `TestCase` | `id`, `feature_id`, `test_key`, `title`, `goal`, `description`, `expected_result`, `priority`, `category` |
| `TestRun` | `id`, `feature_id`, `provider`, `model`, `target_window`, `status`, `passed`, `failed`, `skipped`, `total_tests`, `started_at`, `completed_at`, `created_at` |
| `TestResult` | `id`, `run_id`, `test_case_id`, `status`, `conclusion`, `steps: StepRecord[]`, `steps_executed`, `error`, `created_at` |

**Feature statuses:** `draft` → `context_ready` → `tests_generated`

**`StepRecord` — the unified step shape** (used in both live SSE stream and DB storage):
```typescript
{
  step_number: number;
  action: string;          // raw action name e.g. "left_click"
  type: string;            // generalised type e.g. "click" | "scroll" | "type" | ...
  description: string;     // human-readable reasoning for this step
  target?: string | null;
  value?: string | null;
  reasoning: string;
  success: boolean;
  coordinates?: [number, number] | null;
  confidence?: string | null;
  error?: string | null;
  timestamp: string;       // UTC ISO string
}
```

This shape is the contract between backend (SSE `step` events + DB writes) and frontend (`ActivityEntry`, `StepEvent`). Both live and replay rendering use the same component code because the data shape is identical.

**Cloud backend endpoints relevant to runs/results:**

| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |
|----------|--------|---------|
| `GET /api/v1/test-runs/by-feature/{featureId}` | GET | List all runs for a feature (sorted newest first) |
| `GET /api/v1/test-runs/{runId}/detail` | GET | Full run + all `TestResult` objects with steps |
| `POST /api/v1/test-results/` | POST | Create a `TestResult` (called at test_start, status="running") |
| `POST /api/v1/test-results/{id}/steps` | POST | Atomically `$push` one step to the steps array |
| `PATCH /api/v1/test-results/{id}` | PATCH | Update final status, conclusion, steps_executed |

