## testSuiteExecutionStore — Key State Shape

```typescript
{
  status: 'idle' | 'running' | 'complete' | 'error' | 'aborted';
  tests: TestRun[];          // one entry per test case
  currentTestId: string | null;
  activityLog: ActivityEntry[];  // ALL actions across ALL tests; each entry has testId
                                 // accumulates across tests — never reset per-test
  thinking: string;
  suiteResult: { passed, failed, skipped, total } | null;
  error: string | null;

  // Guided execution
  guidanceNeeded: { testId, question, currentState, confidence? } | null;
  isPaused: boolean;
  isPausePending: boolean;   // true from button press until backend confirms pause
  isAbortPending: boolean;   // true from button press until backend confirms abort
}
```

**Key actions:**
- `setInitialTests(testCases)` — seeds `tests[]` with status `"pending"` (live mode)
- `startExecution(params)` — opens SSE stream, handles all events
- `loadPastRun(testCases, runDetail)` — **replay mode**: populates `tests[]` and `activityLog` from API data, resets all live-execution state
- `reset()` — clears everything back to idle

**Execute page (`execute.tsx`) local state:**
- `selectedTestId` — `null` = follow live current test; `string` = user pinned a specific test to review
- `displayedLog` = `activityLog.filter(e => e.testId === displayedTestId)` — each test's log is isolated
- Store is `reset()` on mount/unmount in live mode; `loadPastRun()` handles init in replay mode

